Title: Salford's Vidot suffers injury blow
Date: Thu, 07 Jan 2016 17:11:01 GMT
DateProc: 1452200351
Link: http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/rugby-league/35256846

![Daniel Vidot](http://ichef.bbci.co.uk/onesport/cps/320/cpsprodpb/170B6/produ
ction/_86609349_gettyimages-475960188.jpg)

Daniel Vidot played at the 2013 Rugby League World Cup for Samoa

Salford Red Devils winger Daniel Vidot could miss up to three months of the
new season because of injury.

Vidot [joined the Super League side](/sport/rugby-league/34775869) this winter
on a two-year contract from Brisbane Broncos, but damaged a shoulder in pre-
season training.

The Samoa international has undergone surgery and the Red Devils expect him to
be out for two to three months.

Meanwhile, owner Marwan Koukash has taken on the chief executive role after
Martin Vickers' exit.


